┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ PHASE 1 — LEGENDRE-CATTANEO SIEVE ([2026-04-04 00:59:48])                                       │
│                                                                                 │
│ PURPOSE:                                                                        │
│ Enumerate all prime-power components (p, 2e) where σ(p^{2e}) has ALL prime    │
│ factors ≡ 1 or 3 (mod 8).  This is the Legendre-Cattaneo obstruction:          │
│                                                                                 │
│   Theorem (Cattaneo 1951 / Hagis 1980):                                        │
│   If N is quasiperfect, σ(N) = 2N+1 ≡ 1 (mod 8), so each σ(p_i^{2e_i})      │
│   must have ALL prime factors q satisfying q ≡ 1 or 3 (mod 8).                 │
│   Any factor q ≡ 5 or 7 (mod 8) invalidates the component.                    │
│                                                                                 │
│ ALGORITHM (Two-Pass Cyclotomic Screening):                                      │
│   For each odd prime p ≤ 250,000 and even exponent 2e ∈ {2..8}:    │
│                                                                                 │
│   1. Compute σ(p^{2e}) = (p^{2e+1} - 1) / (p - 1) via pure-Rust u128       │
│   2. Cyclotomic decomposition: σ(p^{2e}) = ∏_{d|(2e+1)} Φ_d(p)             │
│   3. Trial-divide each Φ_d(p) with early mod-8 exit:                            │
│      a) Trial-divide by small primes (up to 10^7)                               │
│      b) If any factor q ≡ 5 or 7 (mod 8) found → REJECT immediately           │
│      c) Large composite cofactor: use mod-8 subgroup closure property           │
│         {1,3} closed under ×(mod 8), so cofactor ≡ 5,7 → must have bad factor │
│      d) Ambiguous cofactor ≡ 1,3 (mod 8): Pollard ρ fallback to factor         │
│                                                                                 │
│ PARALLELISM: Rayon parallel iterator over all primes.                           │
│ OUTPUT: Surviving components sorted by abundance ratio σ/p^{2e} descending.   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

